      "role": "user",
      "content": "exactly. a prison. and the worst part is that there's no parole. the doctors just keep saying \"manage the symptoms\" or \"try this new routine,\" but they don't get it. they don't get that sometimes i look at the concept of nothingness—just total, silent, painless nothingness—and it feels like the only thing that actually sounds like relief. it feels more like a mercy than anything else.",
